<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Discussions with operators that utilize these type 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
airplanes under 14 CFR part 135 reveal that regular 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maintenance inspections require inspections in this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
area every 200 hours time-in-service (TIS), and that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
there have been no problems with the retractable MLG 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
swivel pins. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The inspection procedures in Piper's maintenance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
manual of the referenced airplanes calls for inspecting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the MLG assembly every 100 hours TIS. The inspection 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedures do not specifically address a teardown 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
inspection of this assembly. At this time, the FAA has 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
