<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A few commenters questioned the apparent lack of a similar exemption for the transaction information reported under
the proposed rule. Section 13(h)(7) provides that ``any information required to be kept or reported'' is exempt from
disclosure under FOIA. Therefore, transaction information reported under the reproposed rule also would be exempt
from disclosure under FOIA. The Commission believes that the non-disclosure of such information also may be covered
by other existing Commission rules.
