<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
C. Agenda 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If the Commission decides to establish a negotiating committee and its charter is approved, it is anticipated that
the Committee's first meeting will take place in March or April, 1994, at the Commission's offices, Washington, DC,
at a building, room, date, and time that will be announced. At this initial meeting, the committee will complete action
on all procedural matters and establish a target date for submission of its recommendations. We expect that the target
date would be no later than July, 1994. We anticipate a publication of a Further Notice of Proposed Rulemaking not later
than October, 1994. 
