<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary proposes to amend the Student Assistance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
General Provisions and Federal Family Education Loan program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulations. These amendments are needed to implement changes in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Higher Education Act of 1965, as amended (HEA), and to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
improve the monitoring and accountability of institutions and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
third-party servicers participating in the student financial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assistance programs authorized by Title IV of the HEA (Title IV, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
HEA programs). The changes would establish requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
governing contracts between institutions and third-party 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicers to administer any aspect of an institution's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
participation in those programs. In addition, the changes would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
strengthen sanctions against institutions for violations of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Title IV, HEA program requirements and establish similar 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sanctions for third-party servicers. The changes also would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establish standards of administrative and financial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
responsibility for third-party servicers that administer any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
aspect of a guaranty agency's or lender's participation in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Family Education Loan programs.
