<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In addition, this section would be amended to specify 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
additional steps that the Secretary may take to insure the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
payment of any liabilities that are owed. Under this section, if 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an institution or third-party servicer owes funds, the Secretary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
may determine that an administrative offset (as provided for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under 34 CFR 30.28) is an appropriate alternative to collect 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
those funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In the case of an institution or third-party servicer that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provides surety or a guarantee for the benefit of the Secretary, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
such as a bond or letter of credit, the Secretary may determine it is necessary to collect from that surety or guarantee
before 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the procedures under subpart H of this part are completed, if 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
circumstances warrant. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary would collect a surety or guarantee before all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
available appeal procedures are completed_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Where the need to provide relief to students or borrowers 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affected by the institution's or third-party servicer's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
actions, as applicable, that led to the assessment of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
liability, is more important than deferring collection 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
activities until after the completion of appeal proceedings 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(for example, when unpaid refunds to the Title IV, HEA 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
programs are identified, the Secretary may collect in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
advance of a final determination or exhaustion of appeal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedures, as the harm to students outweighs deferring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
collection); or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Where the conditions under which a surety or guarantee are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
held do not provide adequate assurances that the surety or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
guarantee will be available for collection through the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
completion of available appeal proceedings. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
These modifications would provide clarification in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulations of the Secretary's existing practice and authority to 
