Section 668.89&blank;Authority and responsibilities of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hearing official.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary proposes to amend this section 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to make clear that a hearing official is bound by all applicable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
statutes and regulations. This change would codify in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulations the existing responsibility of the hearing official. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Section 668.90&blank;Initial and final decisions_Appeals.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section would be amended to add references to third-party 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicers to conform to the proposed changes in the scope of this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart. In addition, paragraph (a)(3) of this section would be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amended to reflect changes proposed under &sect;&sect;668.12 and 668.82 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
dealing with the past performance of individuals, agencies, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
organizations that are affiliated with an institution, including, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as applicable, third-party servicers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary proposes to add a new restriction on a hearing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
official's authority to modify a proposed sanction against an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution or third-party servicer. If a designated department 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
official brings a termination action against an institution or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer for engaging in fraud, and a hearing official finds that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the institution or servicer has engaged in fraud, the hearing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
official must uphold the termination. The examples of fraud 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
listed in this section are the same as those proposed for &sect;668.83 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
concerning emergency action. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary believes that if an institution or third-party 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer engages in fraud involving a Title IV, HEA program, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution's participation in the program should be terminated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or the servicer's eligibility to contract with an institution to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
administer any aspect of that institution's participation in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Title IV, HEA programs, as applicable, should be terminated. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Secretary does not believe that a lesser sanction that permits 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the institution or servicer to continue to participate in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
program or in the case of a third-party servicer to be eligible 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to contract, is a sufficient safeguard against the likely abuse 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of Title IV, HEA program funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary proposes to amend paragraph (c)(1) of this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section so that in a fine, limitation, or termination proceeding, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the hearing official's initial decision automatically becomes the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Secretary's final decision in 30 days (20 days is mandated under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the current regulations) after the initial decision is issued and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
received by both parties unless that initial decision is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
questioned before the Secretary. The Secretary is proposing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
these new timeframes to make them consistent with other reporting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements in this part. The Secretary does not believe that a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ten-day difference in an institution's or servicer's right to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appeal an initial decision would unduly affect the integrity of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Title IV, HEA programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary also proposes to make technical changes in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
paragraph (a)(3)(iv) of this section to correct typographical 
