<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Section 668.92&blank;Fines.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary proposes to add 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
references to third-party servicers in this section to conform to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed changes governing the imposition of fines in other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sections of this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This section would also be amended to provide for the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consideration of the size of the servicer's business (including 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the number of institutions and student accounts served by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer) in determining the amount of a fine against a servicer. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This provision would be similar to the provision already in place 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in this section that requires consideration of the size of an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution in determining the amount of a fine against the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution. The Secretary also proposes to take into account, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the case of a violation by a third-party servicer, the degree 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to which the servicer can provide evidence that the institution 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contributed to that violation and the extent to which repeated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mechanical systemic unintentional errors contributed to that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation. For purposes of this section, repeated mechanical 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
systemic unintentional errors would be counted as a single 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation. This provision was requested by non-Federal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
negotiators to cover cases where errors in computer systems 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
result in multiple violations. The Secretary proposes to adopt 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
these measures in the interest of fairness to a third-party 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer in cases where a minor programming error leads to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hundreds or thousands of violations. While the Secretary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
believes that all resulting losses should be compensated for by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the institution or servicer, fines need not be unduly multiplied. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary specifically invites comment on whether this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provision is sufficiently specific and not excessively broad and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
effectively balances the Federal interest in ensuring compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the realities of computer processing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary also proposes to provide for the consideration 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the amount of liability owed by an institution or third-party 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer on the misuse of Title IV, HEA program funds or refunds 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in determining the gravity of the institution's or servicer's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation, as applicable, of a Title IV requirement. The number 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of students affected by the violation also would be a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consideration in that determination. The Secretary intends these 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provisions to serve as guidelines for evaluating the gravity of a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Section 668.93&blank;Limitation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary proposes to add 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
references to third-party servicers in this section to conform to proposed changes governing the imposition of limitations
in other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sections of this subpart. The Secretary also proposes that a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limitation on a third-party servicer's eligibility to contract 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with institutions to administer any aspect of an institution's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
participation in the Title IV, HEA programs could include a limit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
on the number or size of institutions with which the servicer may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contract, the number of accounts (borrower or loan accounts) that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the servicer may service under contract, an increase or reduction 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the responsibilities allowed or required of the servicer under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a contract, or a requirement for the servicer to obtain surety 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assuring the servicer's ability to meet financial obligations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary believes that these limitations are necessary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to address the probable causes of improprieties in which a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
third-party servicer might engage. By limiting the number or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
size of institutions or accounts that a third-party servicer may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
serve (including, for example, requiring the servicer to transfer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
existing accounts back to the institution) the Secretary may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
address a problem involving the servicer's overextended 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
resources. By limiting the responsibilities performed by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer under a contract, the Secretary may restrict the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer's administration to a particular Title IV, HEA program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
while prohibiting the servicer from administering another 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Title IV, HEA program for which the servicer's past performance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
has been inadequate. By imposing additional responsibilities 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under a third-party servicer's contract, the Secretary may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
require the servicer to use additional safeguards before awarding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or disbursing Title IV, HEA program funds or delivering Federal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Stafford or Federal SLS loan proceeds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

