generally would be parallel to the procedures already established 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that govern appeals by an institution of a final audit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determination or final program review determination. Under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;668.116(e), the Secretary proposes to expand the types of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evidence that an institution or servicer requesting review of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
final audit or final program review determination may submit to a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hearing official to include Department of Education program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
review reports and work papers for program reviews and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institutional or servicer records and other materials (including 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
records and other materials of institutions with which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
servicer has contracts) provided to the Department in response to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a program review. The Secretary also proposes to notify all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institutions with which a third-party servicer contracts of final 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
audit report or final program review determinations. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Secretary believes that an institution that contracts with a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
third-party servicer should be kept informed of any activities 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
between the servicer and the Department that might affect the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
administration of the institution's participation in a Title IV, 
