<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Language of the plan.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The shipboard oil pollution emergency plan must be available on board in English and in the working language of the
master and the officers of the ship, if different.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Plan format.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The plan must contain the following six sections. A seventh non-mandatory section may be included at the shipowner's
discretion:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Introduction.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This section must contain the following introductory text:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``(i) This plan is written in accordance with the requirements of Regulation 26 of Annex I of the International Convention
for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships, 1973, as modified by the Protocol of 1978 relating thereto (MARPOL 73/78).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The purpose of the plan is to provide guidance to the master and officers on board the ship with respect to the steps
to be taken when a pollution incident has occurred or is likely to occur.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The plan contains all information and operational instructions required by the guidelines (Resolution MEPC.54(32)).
The appendices contain names, telephone numbers, telex numbers, etc. of all contacts referenced in the plan, as well
as other reference material.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) This plan has been approved by the Coast Guard and, except as provided below, no alteration or revision may be made
to any part of it without the prior approval of the Coast Guard.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Changes to the seventh section of the plan and the appendices do not require approval by the Coast Guard. The appendices
must be maintained up-to-date by owners, operators, and managers.''
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Preamble.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This section must contain an explanation of the purpose and use of the plan and indicate how the shipboard plan relates
to other shore-based plans.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Reporting requirements.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This section of the plan must include information relating to the following:
