SUMMARY: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
The Coast Guard proposes to expand the boundaries of the safety zone for the Louisiana Offshore Oil Port (LOOP). A deepwater
port safety zone constitutes an area within which the erection of structures or mobile drilling operations for the
exploration for or extraction of oil or gas is prohibited. An expanded safety zone would enlarge the approach to the
terminal portion of the safety zone and provide more unobstructed maneuvering room for vessels arriving and departing
from LOOP. This would reduce the risk of a marine casualty and subsequent pollution.
